rComments: THE WORST class I have took in U of T. Prof a nice person but his lecture is the most monotone and boring one. Marking scheme is screwd up as well, 3 term test and a paper counting for 60% and final for 40%. Many of his theories contradict themselves in different cases so you have to memorize a lot of stuff instead of trying to understand them.

I WISH I had never taken a single course taught by him. Just wanna let you guys know it, i think he disrespects student in various ways. He posts term marks on his little own website with everyone's results on it. Whoever failed the tests will be highlighted in red, you'll see one third of the class being circled out specifically for failure...
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Get ready to read']

rComments: His accent is too thick to understand half the things he says, every single class he interrupts the class to tell someone to get off their phone and it's super awkward, forgets to post lecture slides ahead of the lecture.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Tough grader', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: Try to avoid him for this class. His midterms are very difficult and his classes are very boring. For final exam, he makes you write 5 long answer questions and 20 MCQ's and only gives you 2 hours. It's also worth 40% for a full year course, which is not worth it. Try to avoid him as much as you can. He makes you dislike macroeconomics completely.

His lectures are a never ending 3 hour boredom (2hr lecture + 1 hr. discussion / tutorial), his voice and manner of presenting the material is so annoying that barely anyone makes it to the end of the lecture. He deducts marks for wrong MC answers on the tests (ouch) and there is no hope for a bell curve. Good smart person but an awful prof.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Test heavy', 'Tough grader']

rComments: Let me be very clear. If you are a student coming into your second year, PUSH THIS CLASS OFF UNTIL THIRD YEAR AND SAVE YOUR cGPA. This class is absolutely packed slides full of information. There is no book either, so if you do not understand the slides you are out of luck. Professor doesn't TEACH, he only reads off of slides. AVOID AT ALL COSTS.

He is very inspirational and clear. I go to his class to learn not to only get what i need for his tests. His views on macro policy is very eye-opening for students who have been constantly fed Neo-liberal dogma which does not even hold under the simplest logical examination.

worst class I've taken so far. Guy talks for 2 hours straight , all the slides are packed with info. Hard to follow. Only way to understand curve shift is to look at past test explanations (which are too long also). Accent is very thick. Won't give a mark boost or anything. He repeats the same thing over and over , but will still be very unclear.

First of all, this bloke teaches all the sections for this REQUIRED course. So there's no way you can avoid him. Monotone voice + PP Slide filled with text literally kills all motivation of learning . Only 10 or so out 50 show up to class every week. Spanish accent so bad, it kinda sounds Japanese.  Although knowledgeable, not a very good Prof.
I have taken ECO407 with Gustavo Indart. His course was an eye opener. It was the most interesting economics course I have taken at UofT.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Amazing lectures', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Indart is a very straight forward professor. Attend his lectures, do his past problems and tests and you will get an A. So far, this course has been pretty easy. His slides are very clear and to the point. The only negative I have for Indart is that he can sometimes be monotonous when speaking making it hard to focus on what he's saying in class.
practice problems. past exams help alot
Very nice and helpful prof
His tests are fairly easy as long as you read the textbook and his lecture slides. That being said, going to class is useless because all he does is read off his slides.

Indart's explains every point extremely clear, if you follow his thoughts, then you will understand everything you need to for any tests. He posts most past test online which is really helpful. His answers for the tests are even more helpful.
Having taken this course twice with him I realized that going to class is not necessary since everything is on the lecture slides. Understand them and do past exams and you should be okay.

He is a good prof although he has strong accent. I took it last term and his midterm is not hard. You just need to do all the past tests and understand all the problem sets. I believe u can get a good grade if you put effort on it.
He's great, and his tests are super easy.
hard to understand, lectures are a waste of time since questions are all problem sets which he does not cover in class. reads off the slides.

Indart is organized and gives us all the resources you will need to prepare for the tests. 50% of your midterms consists contents from previous tests, however, they ain't a joke. It actually takes effort to think even though you have done them a million times. As well, I find his test extremely long and therefore, I think endurance is important.
I found Indart to be a great professor. His lectures are very clear and the slides are extremely helpful. His midterms and final exam was very fair! Would definitely recommend him
He really cares about the students and wants to help them succeed. Provides everything the student needs and has very clear lecture slides.
Tests are not super challenging since he gives out previous tests.  Accent is way too thick to understand.  Bell-curves down like there's no tomorrow.

I found that what he taught was almost completely the theoretical concepts. However, when it came to execution with problems, I had no clue even where to begin. Unfortunately, that's all the tests are, which can cause a great deal of frustration. Extremely boring and my least favorite class of first year.

He is one of the worst instructors at U of T. He has Ph.D and specializes in Economics, but he has poor teaching and communication skills. His lecture has no thesis and lack of clarity , yet he made very critical assessments on student's presentations and papers. It is unfortunate that this lecturer has no chance to improve his teaching skills
yes he responds very fast and knows his business, but examns are extremely hard and our first exam has 13percent people get between zero and 13 percent,study hard and you may survive

Indart genuinely takes an interest in students, sometimes taking the initiative to email them himself. He is very approachable and always ready to help. His lectures are also interesting and clear. However, his tests can be needlessly difficult and the textbooks are not useful at all. You really need to put the effort in!
Nice guy for 209, very helpful and responds to emails very very fast. Final was tough though, and focused a lot on the news. Overall nice guy, but def need to put in the effort

- Very strong Italian accent, can't get 70% wth is going on there - Very attentive, reply students' email/questions carefully - Average difficulty, most of the questions come from past papers and assignment, do the crap and you'll do good **Deadly Sure***

A very good prof. Lectures and his slides are word for word. Monotone voice, but he knows his stuff. Do his problem sets and past test, because they are likely to reappear again. He even took the liberty to form study groups for us. A lot of material to learn, so attend all the tutorials and the lectures.
His tests are extremely complicated

He asked trick questions a lot on tests. His questions were so wordy evn my tutor had a hard time understanding. He uses too much flowery language; lacks practical-use questions. I would recommend another professor if ECO is not your strongest. Lots of resources to study from on his site.

He is a nice prof - explains things clearly, willing to answer any questions in class or after class, emails about your progress, etc. That being said, his tests are by no means easy, and attending class is more than necessary. Always take notes as he goes beyond the material posted online, that is, if you don't fall asleep first.
I wonder how many la coste polos he has.
Great prof. Work hard and ask questions when you don't know wtf is going on. Do your**** and you'll do fine.

horrible prof, nice guy. Very hard to follow in class because very very very boring and very very monotone. 2 tests were fair, 1 was unreasonably hard, and exam was ridiculously hard as well. Indart is a great prof when it comes to eco 209.I feel like eco100 is too much of a introduction class to tell the profs apart.
